-- Nomura Hires Lazard's Curtis as U.S. Analyst for Gaming, Hotel Industries
-- Jeff Kearns
-- 2010-07-21T15:09:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-21/nomura-hires-lazard-s-curtis-as-u-s-analyst-for-gaming-hotel-industries.html

          
          
             Nomura Holdings Inc., Japan’s
biggest brokerage, hired  Harry Curtis  of Lazard Capital Markets
as a stock analyst covering the U.S. gaming, hotel and leisure
industries.  
 Curtis will join the company’s U.S. unit, Nomura Securities
International Inc., and be based in New York, according to a
statement from the Tokyo-based company today. He will report to
 Michael Rietbrock , who was hired as head of U.S. equity research
in March.  
